title: Polygon Error: TopologyException: side location conflict

comments.content:
The polygon must be "valid", which among other conditions means edges can't cross each other.  JTS has a GUI tool "TestBuilder" (I think) that can help identify where this is occurring.  To work around this, set validationRule="repairBuffer0"
http://locationtech.github.io/spatial4j/apidocs/org/locationtech/spatial4j/context/jts/ValidationRule.html
comments.author: David Smiley

comments.content: My schema has set validationRule="repairBuffer0". It seems not to fix this problem.
comments.author: samur araujo

comments.content: Then repairConvexHull very likely will, although it'll unfortunately expand the bounds of the shape a lot.
comments.author: David Smiley

comments.content:
Are the repairing applied at query time? Are the repairing applied in the polygon sent in the query?

If I get it right, the repair is apply only at index time, on polygons that are being indexed, right?

The problem I mentioned above happens in the polygons sent as a query parameter.
comments.author: samur araujo

comments.content: The "repairRule" applies universally (index & query) to polygons.  The Spatial4j related parameters are all universal to both.
comments.author: David Smiley
